---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Legacy Archive"
  description="Historical note on the preserved Chinese SCSDA website materials."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell article narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Historical material</p>
      <h2>The old Chinese website is preserved as source material, not copied as-is.</h2>
      <p>
        The previous Chinese SCSDA website has been preserved locally for
        migration, evidence checking and future archival publication. Its pages,
        images and documents are useful historical records, but the English site
        is intentionally redesigned for a different audience.
      </p>
      <p>
        Older pages may contain local policy, incubation, investment,
        public-security or promotional wording that is not appropriate for a UK
        academic-facing site. Those materials should remain in a clearly marked
        archive rather than shaping the main English narrative.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        Future deployment plan: keep the current English site as the main entry
        point and publish selected legacy pages under a labelled archive path
        after link and content review.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
